<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="oa-4-3-meaning-intercept">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Refresh your memory about identifying and explaining intercepts by thinking about these stories. For each story below, say what number the intercept is, and explain what it means in the context of the story.
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    One of Quia Xun's lock machine options has the equation
                    <me>E = 5{,}400 + 0.80L</me>,
                    where <m>E</m> is the total expenditure to produce <m>L</m> locks.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    The equation for the weight <m>W</m> of a truck carrying <m>B</m> bags of grass seed is 
                    <me>W = 3{,}900 + 4.2 B</me>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    If Juan buys the discount card at his favorite local coffee shop, then his total cost <m>T</m> for buying <m>M</m> mugs of coffee is
                    <me>T = 10.00 + 2.90 M</me>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</exploration>